articles.title: Supreme Court seems likely to uphold ACA preventive services mandate - Axios
articles.description: The outcome could decide access to no-cost screenings, tests, HIV drugs and counseling for Americans with private health insurance.
articles.content:
Supreme Court justices appeared inclined Monday to keep the Affordable Care Act's requirement that insurers cover certain recommended preventive services at no cost.
